# Awatif FEM Engine — Explained
### C++ → Mathematical Notation (auto-generated by @{cpp-explain})
---
## 1. Local Stiffness Matrix — Frame Element (12×12)
@{end markdown}

@{cpp-explain}
// Moment of inertia about Z axis
double Iz = getMapValueOrDefault(elementInputs.momentsOfInertiaZ, index, 0.0);
// Moment of inertia about Y axis
double Iy = getMapValueOrDefault(elementInputs.momentsOfInertiaY, index, 0.0);
// Modulus of elasticity
double E = getMapValueOrDefault(elementInputs.elasticities, index, 0.0);
// Cross-sectional area
double A = getMapValueOrDefault(elementInputs.areas, index, 0.0);
// Shear modulus
double G = getMapValueOrDefault(elementInputs.shearModuli, index, 0.0);
// Torsional constant
double J = getMapValueOrDefault(elementInputs.torsionalConstants, index, 0.0);
// Element length
double L = (node1 - node0).norm();
// Axial stiffness coefficient
double EA_L = E * A / L;
// Flexural stiffness Iz (cubic)
double EIz_L3 = E * Iz / (L * L * L);
// Flexural stiffness Iy (cubic)
double EIy_L3 = E * Iy / (L * L * L);
// Torsional stiffness coefficient
double GJ_L = G * J / L;
// Flexural stiffness Iz (quadratic)
double EIz_L2 = E * Iz / (L * L);
// Flexural stiffness Iy (quadratic)
double EIy_L2 = E * Iy / (L * L);
// Flexural stiffness Iz (linear)
double EIz_L = E * Iz / L;
// Flexural stiffness Iy (linear)
double EIy_L = E * Iy / L;
@{end cpp-explain}

@{markdown}
